Package: ecoDrift
Title: Modeling Change in Community Composition with Hubbell's Neutral Theory
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: 
    person("James", "Saulsbury", , "jgsaulsbury@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre", 
    "cph"))
Description: Fit neutral (drift) models to timeseries of fossil community composition. 
  Based on a simple version of Hubbell's (2001) Unified Neutral Theory of Biodiversity.
  Useful for measuring rates of ecological change, fitting a variety of drift models
  to data, and visualizing relative abundances and fitted models.
